# Component Development Standards

## Structure
- Use functional components with hooks exclusively
- Follow atomic design pattern:
  - atoms/ (basic UI elements)
  - molecules/ (combinations of atoms)
  - organisms/ (complex components)
  - templates/ (screen layouts)
- Keep components under 150 lines
- Extract logic to custom hooks when appropriate

## Props and State
- Use TypeScript interfaces for all props
- Provide default props for optional values
- Use React.memo for performance-critical components
- Avoid prop drilling with Context API

## Styling
- Use React Native StyleSheet for styling
- Define theme constants in a central location
- Implement responsive layouts with flexbox
- Support both light and dark modes

## Performance
- Use FlatList for long lists
- Implement image optimization
- Handle loading states with skeleton screens
- Add error boundaries for critical components
